      "comment": "CHAROS NOBLE (1) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at this track over 297m behind Charos Dream (18.43) in a Grade 5/6. Has performed well from this box with a win and six minor placings to his name from 13 starts. Tough to beat if on-song. ROCKIN' KINLOCH (8) pinged the lids and was in the firing line early but drifted out of it when 5th at Cannington in Grade 5/6 company. A big run wouldn't surprise. ASTON CREMA (2) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when fourth (18.19), beaten 9 lengths. Key runner on best form. NITRO NED (6) is new to this track but not to be underestimated.",
